UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. S. Sam CALDWELL and Nancy Sue Brown, Defendants-Appellees. No. 84-8787. United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Jan. 2, 1986. Jere W. Morehead, Robert S. Stubbs, Asst. U.S. Attys., Atlanta, Ga., for plaintiff-appellant. Christopher A. Townley, Rossville, Ga., for N. Brown. William A. Morrison, Atlanta, Ga., for S. Caldwell.

*902Before KRAVITCH and HATCHETT, Circuit Judges, and WRIGHT *, Senior Circuit Judge.

Honorable Eugene A. Wright, Senior U.S. Circuit Judge of the Ninth Circuit, sitting by designation.

 BY THE COURT:

The parties joint motion to dismiss this appeal and vacate the opinion rendered on September 24,1985, 771 F.2d 1485, is granted.
